67 class QuadrotorDecoupled6DRelKinematics
68  : public RelativeDynamics<PositionVelocity, QuadrotorControl,
69  PositionVelocity, VectorXd> {
70 public:
71  ~QuadrotorDecoupled6DRelKinematics() {}
72  explicit QuadrotorDecoupled6DRelKinematics()
73  : RelativeDynamics<PositionVelocity, QuadrotorControl, PositionVelocity,
74  VectorXd>() {}
75 
76  // Derived classes must be able to give the time derivative of relative state
77  // as a function of current state and control of each system.
78  inline std::unique_ptr<RelativeState<PositionVelocity, PositionVelocity>>
79  Evaluate(const PositionVelocity &tracker_x, const QuadrotorControl &tracker_u,
80  const PositionVelocity &planner_x, const VectorXd &planner_u) const {
81  if (planner_u.size() != PositionVelocity::ConfigurationDimension())
82  std::runtime_error("Bad planner control size.");
83 
84  // TODO(@jaime): confirm that this works. I set things up so things like
85  // this should work.
86  const QuadrotorDecoupled6D quad_dynamics;
87  const Kinematics<PositionVelocity> quad_kinematics;
88  return std::unique_ptr<PositionVelocityRelPositionVelocity>(
89  new PositionVelocityRelPositionVelocity(
90  quad_dynamics.Evaluate(tracker_x, tracker_u),
91  quad_kinematics.Evaluate(planner_x, planner_u)));
92  }
93 
94  // Derived classes must be able to compute an optimal control given
95  // the gradient of the value function at the relative state specified
96  // by the given system states, provided abstract control bounds.
97  inline QuadrotorControl OptimalControl(
98  const PositionVelocity &tracker_x, const PositionVelocity &planner_x,
99  const RelativeState<PositionVelocity, PositionVelocity> &value_gradient,
100  const ControlBound<QuadrotorControl> &tracker_u_bound,
101  const ControlBound<VectorXd> &planner_u_bound) const {
102  // Get internal state of value gradient and map tracker control (negative)
103  // coefficients to QuadrotorControl, so we get a negative gradient.
104  const auto &cast = static_cast<const PositionVelocityRelPositionVelocity &>(
105  value_gradient);
106 
107  const auto &grad = cast.State();
108  QuadrotorControl negative_grad;
109  negative_grad.yaw_rate = 0.0;
110  negative_grad.pitch = -grad.Vx();
111  negative_grad.roll = grad.Vy();
112  negative_grad.thrust = -grad.Vz();
113 
114  // Project onto tracker control bound and make sure to zero out yaw_rate.
115  QuadrotorControl c = tracker_u_bound.ProjectToSurface(negative_grad);
116  c.yaw_rate = 0.0;
117 
118  return c;
119  }
120 }; //\class QuadrotorDecoupled6DRelKinematics
